      • addVertex

        public TitanVertex addVertex(Long vertexId)
        Description copied from interface: TitanTransaction
        Creates a new vertex in the graph with the given vertex id. Note, that an exception is thrown if the vertex id is not a valid Titan vertex id or if a vertex with the given id already exists.

        Custom id setting must be enabled via the configuration option GraphDatabaseConfiguration.ALLOW_SETTING_VERTEX_ID_KEY.

        Use TitanId.toVertexId(long) to construct a valid Titan vertex id from a user id.

        Parameters:
        vertexId - vertex id of the vertex to be created
        Returns:
        New vertex

      • indexQuery

        public TitanIndexQuery indexQuery(String indexName,
                         String query)
        Description copied from interface: TitanTransaction
        Returns a TitanIndexQuery to query for vertices or edges against the specified indexing backend using the given query string. The query string is analyzed and answered by the underlying storage backend.

        Note, that using indexQuery will may ignore modifications in the current transaction.

        Parameters:
        indexName - Name of the indexing backend to query as configured
        query - Query string
        Returns:
        TitanIndexQuery object to query the index directly

      • commit

        public void commit()
        Description copied from interface: TitanTransaction
        Commits and closes the transaction.

        Will attempt to persist all modifications which may result in exceptions in case of persistence failures or lock contention.
        The call releases data structures if possible. All element references (e.g. vertex objects) retrieved through this transaction are stale after the transaction closes and should no longer be used.

      • rollback

        public void rollback()
        Description copied from interface: TitanTransaction
        Aborts and closes the transaction. Will discard all modifications.

        The call releases data structures if possible. All element references (e.g. vertex objects) retrieved through this transaction are stale after the transaction closes and should no longer be used.

        public boolean hasModifications()
        Description copied from interface: TitanTransaction
